564
00:43:56,482 --> 00:43:58,084
[SPEAKER_03]: Why don't you stand by your record?

565
00:43:58,204 --> 00:43:58,785
[SPEAKER_03]: You'll see it.

566
00:43:58,805 --> 00:44:01,268
[SPEAKER_14]: Record levels of taxes on working people.

567
00:44:01,508 --> 00:44:04,152
[SPEAKER_03]: 26 separate tax hikes in the last parliament.

568
00:44:04,172 --> 00:44:09,598
[SPEAKER_02]: We've heard overnight about 12 new taxes that Labour are going to bring in.

569
00:44:09,618 --> 00:44:10,580
[SPEAKER_02]: It's not rubbish.

570
00:44:10,680 --> 00:44:10,980
[SPEAKER_02]: That's rubbish.

571
00:44:11,000 --> 00:44:12,061
[SPEAKER_03]: Absolutely rubbish.

572
00:44:12,142 --> 00:44:15,906
[SPEAKER_03]: We've absolutely guaranteed we will not raise taxes for working people in this country.

573
00:44:15,926 --> 00:44:16,547
[SPEAKER_03]: Can we have a shot?

574
00:44:16,527 --> 00:44:18,289
[SPEAKER_03]: Close that gap.

575
00:44:18,309 --> 00:44:20,852
[SPEAKER_03]: £2,000 per working household.

576
00:44:22,495 --> 00:44:25,478
[SPEAKER_03]: Which policies are you going to take out of your manifesto?

577
00:44:25,618 --> 00:44:31,065
[SPEAKER_03]: We've been clear how we would pay for our manifesto.

578
00:44:31,246 --> 00:44:32,367
[SPEAKER_06]: It's time to hear from the others.

