00:51:00,372 --> 00:51:12,364
[SPEAKER_02]: Well... LAUGHTER This is why the Prime Minister made the very clear pledges that he did, and you can measure the progress being made against them.

652
00:51:13,728 --> 00:51:15,330
[SPEAKER_02]: We are making progress in this country.

653
00:51:15,350 --> 00:51:19,076
[SPEAKER_02]: We have been through some very hard times, but the recovery is there.

654
00:51:19,116 --> 00:51:23,463
[SPEAKER_02]: What we must ensure is that that is not choked off.

655
00:51:23,863 --> 00:51:27,749
[SPEAKER_02]: And we must ensure that your taxes are being lowered.

656
00:51:28,350 --> 00:51:30,333
[SPEAKER_02]: That is the pledge that we make to you.

657
00:51:30,934 --> 00:51:36,462
[SPEAKER_02]: And that is what we have been doing with national insurance cuts that we have seen this year.

658
00:51:36,442 --> 00:51:37,984
[SPEAKER_02]: That is what you need.

659
00:51:38,545 --> 00:51:40,767
[SPEAKER_02]: It's not just your taxes that I'm worried about.

660
00:51:40,828 --> 00:51:45,053
[SPEAKER_02]: I'm worried about my constituents being able to afford a Labour government.

