01:20:05,701 --> 01:20:11,127
[SPEAKER_01]: Again, Labour at a UK level, hoping to become the next government, say no, no chance.

1070
01:20:11,608 --> 01:20:13,510
[SPEAKER_06]: Briefly, Carla, before I turn to Stephen Flynn.

1071
01:20:13,760 --> 01:20:20,089
[SPEAKER_13]: I've signed the Citizens UK pledge for a counsellor in every school to help with young people's mental health and with youth violence.

1072
01:20:20,529 --> 01:20:22,532
[SPEAKER_13]: Will the others on the panel today join me?

1073
01:20:23,754 --> 01:20:26,658
[SPEAKER_14]: Well, we already committed that we'd have mental health services in schools.

1074
01:20:26,818 --> 01:20:28,801
[SPEAKER_14]: That's one of our commitments.

1075
01:20:28,821 --> 01:20:34,829
[SPEAKER_06]: Stephen Flynn, on the broader question of policing, police officer numbers in Scotland are at the lowest level since 2008.

1076
01:20:35,370 --> 01:20:39,936
[SPEAKER_06]: Now, police in Scotland are not investigating every low-level crime.

1077
01:20:40,237 --> 01:20:46,906
[SPEAKER_11]: And thankfully, of course, Nick, in relation to your direct question, I remember the figures correctly.

1078
01:20:47,167 --> 01:20:51,713
[SPEAKER_11]: Serious knife crime in Scotland is comparatively low compared with many other areas.

1079
01:20:51,833 --> 01:20:56,400
[SPEAKER_11]: Now that's not to be complacent, because as a dad, I share your concerns.

1080
01:20:56,440 --> 01:20:58,583
[SPEAKER_11]: I worry about what the future holds for my kids.

1081
01:20:58,563 --> 01:21:01,991
[SPEAKER_11]: But ultimately the solution lies in what Reem has said.

1082
01:21:02,532 --> 01:21:07,985
[SPEAKER_11]: What we need to do is make sure that we are investing in the areas that need support the most.

1083
01:21:08,005 --> 01:21:16,925
[SPEAKER_11]: Poverty is a major driver behind this and Westminster has failed generations of young people by not providing them with the hope for a better future.

1084
01:21:16,945 --> 01:21:17,787
[SPEAKER_11]: So they turn

1085
01:21:17,767 --> 01:21:20,970
[SPEAKER_11]: to violence when they perhaps shouldn't.

1086
01:21:21,050 --> 01:21:32,182
[SPEAKER_11]: And I think that's something we should all reflect upon going into this general election, where £18 billion of public sector cuts are coming down the line and the future Labour government has no answers.

1087
01:21:32,443 --> 01:21:39,450
[SPEAKER_06]: But this question was about how the parties are going to protect future generations, like Nick O'Donnell's son.

1088
01:21:39,991 --> 01:21:46,137
[SPEAKER_06]: How can he feel confident of that if someone in a similar position in Scotland see the police not investigating every crime?

1089
01:21:46,117 --> 01:22:01,765
[SPEAKER_11]: Well, of course, as I've already outlined, as I understand it to be the case, serious knife crime instances in Scotland are comparatively low in comparison to elsewhere, but our police officer numbers are of course still higher than when we came into government.

1090
01:22:01,825 --> 01:22:03,248
[SPEAKER_11]: Again, if I understand

1091
01:22:03,228 --> 01:22:17,423
[SPEAKER_11]: correctly but there's a wider picture to be had here and that means police officers working with local communities, working with schools, working with our young people to offer them hope and optimism for the future and I'm afraid that Westminster doesn't offer that hope and optimism right now.

1092
01:22:20,508 --> 01:22:21,169
[SPEAKER_06]: Nigel Farage.

1093
01:22:22,151 --> 01:22:27,281
[SPEAKER_08]: Yeah, look, you know, again, I just think a whole approach to crime is wrong.

1094
01:22:27,662 --> 01:22:30,006
[SPEAKER_08]: Low-level crime is rapidly growing.

1095
01:22:30,767 --> 01:22:32,851
[SPEAKER_08]: Street-level crime is rapidly growing.

1096
01:22:33,473 --> 01:22:39,023
[SPEAKER_08]: And, you know, the old theories, the old theories about New York and how it was cleaned up, it was if you deal with the stuff at the bottom,

1097
01:22:39,003 --> 01:22:39,384
[SPEAKER_08]: i.e.

1098
01:22:39,424 --> 01:22:45,215
[SPEAKER_08]: people carrying knives, shoplifting, graffiti, broken windows, you might just deal with the more serious stuff.

1099
01:22:45,235 --> 01:22:51,025
[SPEAKER_08]: I think we also should add into all of this the blight of drugs and drug gangs in our cities.

1100
01:22:51,146 --> 01:22:58,800
[SPEAKER_08]: That whole culture, it has been absolutely disastrous and nobody, but nobody has yet found the answer to that.

1101
01:22:58,780 --> 01:23:01,924
[SPEAKER_06]: OK, well, that was our final question.

1102
01:23:01,984 --> 01:23:09,312
[SPEAKER_06]: So I'm going to thank you all for your responses to all of those here in the audience who have shared their questions with us.

1103
01:23:09,973 --> 01:23:21,025
[SPEAKER_06]: But it is time now to go to the parties final thoughts and that for that they have been given 30 seconds for a final thought from each of them and the order

1104
01:23:21,005 --> 01:23:25,225
[SPEAKER_06]: of those final thoughts, those final statements was chosen earlier by lots.

1105
01:23:25,245 --> 01:23:29,023
[SPEAKER_06]: So let us go to the first of those and it's from Angela Rayner.

1106
01:23:30,539 --> 01:23:34,283
[SPEAKER_14]: After 14 years of chaos, it's time for change.

1107
01:23:35,064 --> 01:23:37,547
[SPEAKER_14]: Keir Starmer has changed the Labour Party.

1108
01:23:38,107 --> 01:23:51,102
[SPEAKER_14]: Our fully costed plan for Britain will secure our economy, will bring down NHS waiting times with 40,000 new appointments every week, and will secure our borders, not with gimmicks, but with a credible plan to smash the gangs.

1109
01:23:51,582 --> 01:23:56,648
[SPEAKER_14]: We'll create great British energy, bringing down bills and creating thousands of well-paid jobs.

1110
01:23:56,628 --> 01:24:02,446
[SPEAKER_14]: will boost neighbourhood police to tackle anti-social behaviour and will hire 6,500 new teachers.

1111
01:24:02,887 --> 01:24:05,355
[SPEAKER_14]: So if you want change, vote Labour.

1112
01:24:08,980 --> 01:24:12,965
[SPEAKER_11]: The Tories are finished so the choice is simple.

1113
01:24:12,985 --> 01:24:17,992
[SPEAKER_11]: Who do voters best trust to put Scotland's interests first in Westminster?

1114
01:24:18,032 --> 01:24:21,156
[SPEAKER_11]: Now in the SNP we know what it is that we believe in.

1115
01:24:21,176 --> 01:24:30,027
[SPEAKER_11]: Investment in our NHS, action on the cost of living crisis, rejoining the European single market and creating economic growth by

1116
01:24:30,007 --> 01:24:32,850
[SPEAKER_11]: delivering on net zero.

1117
01:24:33,171 --> 01:24:42,481
[SPEAKER_11]: Unlike the Labour Party, we will never, ever get comfortable with the Westminster status quo and we will always fight for Scotland's right to choose its own future.

1118
01:24:42,521 --> 01:24:45,524
[SPEAKER_11]: So on the 4th of July, vote to put Scotland's interests first.

1119
01:24:45,845 --> 01:24:46,465
[SPEAKER_11]: Vote SNP.

1120
01:24:47,427 --> 01:24:47,987
[SPEAKER_13]: Carla Denyer.

1121
01:24:49,128 --> 01:24:52,712
[SPEAKER_13]: We can all see the Tories are toast, thank goodness.

1122
01:24:52,732 --> 01:24:57,718
[SPEAKER_13]: But we deserve better than a Labour Party that is offering more of the same.

1123
01:24:57,901 --> 01:25:01,464
[SPEAKER_13]: Angela says that Keir has changed the Labour Party, and she's right.

1124
01:25:02,165 --> 01:25:03,667
[SPEAKER_13]: He's changed them into the Conservatives.

1125
01:25:04,648 --> 01:25:07,070
[SPEAKER_13]: Frankly, our children deserve better.

1126
01:25:07,851 --> 01:25:11,834
[SPEAKER_13]: The Green Party is on the cusp of breaking through in seats up and down the country.

1127
01:25:12,435 --> 01:25:20,983
[SPEAKER_13]: Green MPs will never stop defending our future, protecting our NHS from privatisation and pushing the next Labour government to do better.

1128
01:25:21,664 --> 01:25:24,066
[SPEAKER_13]: We deserve real hope and real change.

1129
01:25:24,707 --> 01:25:25,067
[SPEAKER_13]: Vote Green.

1130
01:25:26,068 --> 01:25:26,929
[SPEAKER_06]: Reena Pureworth.

1131
01:25:29,356 --> 01:25:40,306
[SPEAKER_01]: This evening, I've been able to stand up for Wales, yes, but also for a different kind of politics that hopefully has been able to feel relevant wherever you are.

1132
01:25:40,526 --> 01:25:42,708
[SPEAKER_01]: My vision is a positive one.

1133
01:25:42,728 --> 01:25:44,910
[SPEAKER_01]: This isn't as good as it gets.

1134
01:25:45,070 --> 01:25:49,855
[SPEAKER_01]: The Conservatives are gone, they are finished, and it can't come quickly enough.

1135
01:25:50,715 --> 01:25:58,182
[SPEAKER_01]: But there is a real chance here to send Labour a message to stop taking Wales for granted.

1136
01:25:58,634 --> 01:26:03,561
[SPEAKER_01]: It is true that communities throughout the UK feel as if they are being ignored.

1137
01:26:03,581 --> 01:26:05,564
[SPEAKER_01]: Well, I won't let Wales be.

1138
01:26:05,664 --> 01:26:08,247
[SPEAKER_01]: So vote Plaid Cymru on the 4th of July.

1139
01:26:10,691 --> 01:26:17,841
[SPEAKER_02]: Penny Mordaunt, we've come through tough times and now there is a choice to be made.

1140
01:26:19,022 --> 01:26:27,274
[SPEAKER_02]: You can choose Angela Rayner and Keir Starmer and get higher taxes, higher bills and have your pension raided.

1141
01:26:27,794 --> 01:26:31,481
[SPEAKER_02]: or you can stick with us and the plan that is working.

1142
01:26:32,423 --> 01:26:33,846
[SPEAKER_02]: We will cut your taxes.

1143
01:26:34,448 --> 01:26:36,271
[SPEAKER_02]: We will protect your pension.

1144
01:26:37,033 --> 01:26:39,919
[SPEAKER_02]: And we will defend this nation.

1145
01:26:41,442 --> 01:26:45,550
[SPEAKER_02]: For a more secure future, vote Conservative.

1146
01:26:46,795 --> 01:26:51,920
[SPEAKER_15]: Our country is crying out for change, and it's not hard to see why.

1147
01:26:52,981 --> 01:26:57,106
[SPEAKER_15]: Under this Conservative government, everything feels broken.

1148
01:26:57,907 --> 01:27:00,329
[SPEAKER_15]: Nothing works.

1149
01:27:00,349 --> 01:27:14,524
[SPEAKER_15]: Under Ed Davies' leadership, the Liberal Democrats will fix our NHS and social care, tackle the cost-of-living crisis, and put an end to the scandal of filthy raw sewage being dumped in our rivers and streams.

1150
01:27:14,504 --> 01:27:22,740
[SPEAKER_15]: Every vote for the Liberal Democrats is a vote for a fair deal and a vote to help deliver the change that we all so desperately want and need.

1151
01:27:24,043 --> 01:27:24,664
[SPEAKER_06]: Nigel Farage.

1152
01:27:25,165 --> 01:27:27,309
[SPEAKER_08]: Unlike the other six, I don't need an autocue.

1153
01:27:27,890 --> 01:27:29,914
[SPEAKER_08]: I'm here because I believe in what I believe in.

1154
01:27:30,569 --> 01:27:32,251
[SPEAKER_08]: Our politics isn't working.

1155
01:27:32,271 --> 01:27:36,056
[SPEAKER_08]: You've heard these pathetic arguments tonight between the two big parties.

1156
01:27:36,196 --> 01:27:37,498
[SPEAKER_08]: Really, there isn't much difference.

1157
01:27:37,558 --> 01:27:39,801
[SPEAKER_08]: But electorally, Labour are going to win.

1158
01:27:40,322 --> 01:27:44,507
[SPEAKER_08]: The debate is, who forms the opposition in the next Parliament?

1159
01:27:44,607 --> 01:27:46,911
[SPEAKER_08]: Who fights for the rights of ordinary British people?

1160
01:27:47,011 --> 01:27:48,933
[SPEAKER_08]: Who fights to control our borders?

1161
01:27:48,993 --> 01:27:51,557
[SPEAKER_08]: Who fights for men and women running small businesses?

1162
01:27:52,197 --> 01:27:57,424
[SPEAKER_08]: Reform UK is about to become a political phenomenon, an historic one.

1163
01:27:57,484 --> 01:28:00,188
[SPEAKER_08]: So I urge you, join the revolt.

1164
01:28:01,535 --> 01:28:02,438
[SPEAKER_06]: Thank you very much.

1165
01:28:02,578 --> 01:28:03,661
[SPEAKER_06]: Thank you all.

1166
01:28:04,764 --> 01:28:06,449
[SPEAKER_06]: And with that, we end it.

1167
01:28:06,509 --> 01:28:08,956
[SPEAKER_06]: That is it from the BBC election debate.

1168
01:28:08,976 --> 01:28:14,652
[SPEAKER_06]: From all of us here in the radio theatre, our audience, and thank you to all the politicians who took part.

1169
01:28:14,713 --> 01:28:15,735
[SPEAKER_06]: Thank you for being with us.

1170
01:28:15,996 --> 01:28:16,658
[SPEAKER_06]: Good night.

1171
01:28:34,255 --> 01:28:38,899
APPLAUSE

